  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6599.59 sitting just below the massive +6.78B gamma wall at 6600, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above this level as they're long gamma and need to hedge delta. The PIN regime combined with 17.7B total GEX creates strong mean-reverting forces, while the recent GEX surge (64.8% 1-min change) indicates heavy options flow that should amplify these stabilizing dynamics. Key inflection points are the 6600 resistance wall above and the 6500 negative gamma floor below—a break under 6500 flips dealers into buy-high/sell-low mode and opens downside toward the 6400 amplifying level.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect strong resistance at 6600 with pullback pressure toward 6500-6550 range.",
